<xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" n="sb;4;7353" targOrder="U" to="DITTO" type="reprint from">SB4,7353</xref></head><div lang="grc" part="N" type="edition"><div n="r" part="N" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="1"/>Ἀπολινᾶρις <choice><corr>Ταήσει</corr><sic>ταησι</sic></choice> τῇ <choice><corr>μητρὶ</corr><sic>μητρει</sic></choice> καὶ κυρίᾳ 

    <lb n="2"/>πολλὰ χαίρειν. πρὸ μὲν πάντων εὔχομαί σε 

    <lb n="3"/><choice><corr>ὑγιαίνειν</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">υ</hi>γειαινειν</sic></choice> <choice><corr>καὶ ἐγὼ</corr><sic>καγω</sic></choice> αὐτὸς <choice><corr>ὑγιαίνω</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">υ</hi>γειαινω</sic></choice> καὶ τὸ προσκύνη-

    <lb n="4"/>μά σου ποιῶ παρὰ τοῖς ἐνθάδε θεοῖς. <choice><corr>γινώσκειν</corr><sic>γεινωσκειν</sic></choice> σε 

    <lb n="5"/>θέλω, μήτηρ, ὅτι ἐρρωμένος ἐγενόμην εἰς Ῥώμην 

    <lb n="6"/>Παχὼν μηνὶ <num value="25">κε</num> καὶ ἐκληρώθην εἰς Μισηνούς. 

    <lb n="7"/>οὔπω δὲ τὴν <choice><corr>κε<supplied cert="high" reason="omitted">ν</supplied>τυρίαν</corr><sic>κετυριαν</sic></choice> μου ἔγνων· οὐ γὰρ <choice><corr>ἀπε-

    <lb n="8"/>ληλύθειν</corr><sic>απεληλυτειν</sic></choice> εἰς Μισηνοὺς ὅτε σοι τὴν ἐπιστολὴν ταύτην 

    <lb n="9"/>ἔγραφον. ἐρωτῶ σε οὖν, μήτηρ, σεαυτῇ πρόσεχε, 

    <lb n="10"/>μηδὲν δίσταζε περὶ ἐμοῦ· ἐγὼ γὰρ εἰς καλὸν τό-

    <lb n="11"/>πον ἦλθον. καλῶς δὲ <choice><corr>ποιήσ<supplied cert="high" reason="omitted">εις</supplied></corr><sic>ποιης</sic></choice> <choice><corr>γράψασά</corr><sic>γραψασσα</sic></choice> μοι ἐπιστο-

    <lb n="12"/>λὴν πε<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ρ</supplied>ὶ τῆς σωτηρίας σου καὶ τῶν ἀδελφῶν μου καὶ 

    <lb n="13"/>τῶν σῶν πάντων. καὶ <choice><corr>ἐγὼ</corr><sic>γω</sic></choice> εἴ τινα ἐὰν εὕρω γράφω 

    <lb n="14"/>σοι· οὐ μὴ ὀκνήσω σοι <choice><corr>γράφειν</corr><sic>γραφιν</sic></choice>. ἀσπάζομαι τοὺς ἀ-

    <lb n="15"/>δελφούς μου πολλὰ καὶ Ἀπολινᾶριν καὶ τὰ τέ-

    <lb n="16"/>κνα αὐτοῦ καὶ Καραλᾶν καὶ τὰ τέκνα αὐτοῦ. 

    <lb n="17"/>ἀσπάζ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ο</supplied>μαι Πτολεμαῖν καὶ Πτολεμαείδα καὶ τὰ 

    <lb n="18"/>τέκν<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">α</supplied> αὐτῆς καὶ Ἡρακλοῦν καὶ τὰ τέκνα αὐτῆς. 

    <lb n="19"/>ἀσπάζομαι τοὺς φιλοῦντάς σε πάντας κατ᾽ ὄνο-

    <lb n="20"/>μα. 

    <lb n="21"/>ἐρρῶσθαί σε εὔχομαι. 
</ab></div><div n="v" part="N" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="22"/><expan>ἀπόδ<ex cert="high">ος</ex></expan> εἰς Καρανίδα <g type="x"/> <choice><corr>Ταήσει</corr><sic>ταησι</sic></choice> ἀπὸ Ἀπολιναρίου <choice><corr>υἱοῦ</corr><sic>υειου</sic></choice> 

    <lb n="23"/><g type="x"/> Μισηνάτου. </ab></div></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="200" notBefore="101" type="textDate">II</date></p></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Mich.</title><biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">491</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">27101</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP"><series>0163</series>; <biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">491</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0163;8;491" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p><bibl type="illustration">Class. Phil. 22, 1927, Plate II nach S. 242</bibl><bibl type="illustration">White, Ancient Letters, S. 163</bibl></p></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" subtype="otherPublications" type="bibliography"><head>Andere Publikationen</head><listBibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">SB IV 7353</bibl><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">Sel. Pap. I 111</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" subtype="translations" type="bibliography"><head>Übersetzungen</head><listBibl lang="de"><head lang="de">Deutsch:</head><bibl type="translations">B. Palme,</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang=""><head lang="de">in:</head><bibl type="translations">Festschrift L. Aigner-Foresti (2006), S. 290, Anm. 41.</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang="en"><head lang="de">Englisch:</head><bibl type="translations">Winter, Life and Letters (1933), S. 41</bibl><bibl type="translations">White, Ancient Letters (1986), 104B</bibl><bibl type="translations">Rowlandson, Women and Society (1998), 105.</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang="fr"><head lang="de">Französisch:</head><bibl type="translations">Schubert, Vivre en Égypte (2000), S. 101-102, Nr. 22</bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" subtype="locations" type="history"><p><placeName cert="high" type="ancientFindspot">Rom</placeName></p></div><div n="meta.27101" part="N" type="figure"><p><figure href="http://wwwapp.cc.columbia.edu/ldpd/app/apis/item?mode=item&amp;key=michigan.apis.2221"><figDesc>Abbildung im Internet</figDesc></figure></p></div></body></text></TEI.2>